          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. Loss-of-function variants in SMAD4 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 16152648, 16436638, 22810475). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with SMAD4-related disease. This variant is not present in population databases (ExAC no frequency). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Leu148Argfs*9) in the SMAD4 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product.</Comment>
